<p>On a train bound, we presumed, for the Somme. Since than (on account of the push at Messines perhaps) we hear that they have been returned to the Northern Sector, so we may see Caestre again yet.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;X&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;x&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;x&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;x<br/>Yesterday we heard that Fritz had begun a push from Armenteres to the Ypres-Comines Canal sector (from the paper). Today the startling news arrived that he had pushed us back almost to Bailleul</p>
